50|$|The United Nations: the Fighting Discrimination Program was {{initiated}} {{in the aftermath}} of the 2001 Durban UN World Conference Against Racism (WCAR), which was attended by senior staff of Human Rights First. Hence, the UN is an important stage for the Program's initiatives. Apart from engaging in various advocacy opportunities at the UN, Fighting Discrimination has also played a role in moving the venue for the <b>Durban</b> <b>Review</b> Conference from South Africa to the Geneva, Switzerland. Human Rights First representatives took part in several Preparatory Committee Meetings and will be present at the <b>Durban</b> <b>Review</b> in 2009.|$|R
